    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NRACH indication packing to include instance length fields\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_nrach_indication` function in the NFAPI P7 interface was not correctly packing the NRACH indication PDUs because it was missing the required 2-byte instance length field before each PDU's TLVs. This caused unpacking failures when the VNF tried to process NRACH indications from the PNF.\n\nThe issue occurred because the unpack function expected each PDU to have:\n- 2 bytes for instance length\n- 4 bytes for TLV header (tag + length)  \n- 6 bytes for REL13 data content\n\nBut the pack function was only writing the TLV without the instance length field.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/src/nfapi_p7.c`: Modified `pack_nrach_indication_body_value` function to:\n  1. Write a placeholder for the instance length before packing each PDU's TLVs\n  2. Pack the TLVs for that PDU using the existing `pack_tlv` function\n  3. Calculate the actual instance length (total bytes after the instance length field)\n  4. Update the placeholder with the calculated instance length\n\nThis ensures that the packed data format matches what the unpack function expects, resolving the issue where calling `pack_nrach_indication()` was not producing correctly formatted messages that could be successfully unpacked by the receiving end.\n"
}